df['Hours'] = df['DateHour'].dt.hour

df.groupby('DateHour')[['Sessions','Users']].sum().plot(ax=plt.gca(), color=colors)
plt.title('Sessions and Users over time')
plt.xlabel('Date Hour')
plt.ylabel('Count')
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

Engaged vs. non Engagged sessions¶

In [47]:
session_df=df.groupby('channel group')[['Sessions','Engaged sessions']].sum().reset_index()
session_df['Non engaged'] = session_df['Sessions'] - session_df['Engaged sessions']
session_df_melted = session_df.melt(id_vars = 'channel group', value_vars= ['Engaged sessions', 'Non engaged'])

plt.figure(figsize = (8,5))
sns.barplot(data = session_df_melted, x= 'channel group', y='value', hue = 'variable', palette = 'flare')
plt.title(' Engaged vs. Non- Engaged sessions')
plt.xticks(rotation = 45)
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

Traffic by Hour & Channel¶

In [48]:
plt.figure(figsize=(12, 8))
ax = sns.heatmap(
    data,
    cmap='rocket_r',
    linewidths=0.5,
    cbar_kws={'label': 'Sessions'},
    annot=False  
)

# Loop over the data to add smart contrast annotations
for y in range(data.shape[0]):       # rows
    for x in range(data.shape[1]):   # columns
        val = data.iloc[y, x]
        if val != 0:  # Optional: skip zeros
            # Get background color at this cell
            rgb = ax.collections[0].get_facecolors()[y * data.shape[1] + x]
            brightness = np.dot(rgb[:3], [0.299, 0.587, 0.114])  # Perceived brightness
            text_color = 'white' if brightness < 0.5 else 'black'

            ax.text(
                x + 0.5, y + 0.5, f'{int(val)}',
                ha='center', va='center',
                color=text_color,
                fontsize=10
            )

plt.title("Traffic by Hour & Channel", fontsize=16)
plt.xlabel("Channel Group", fontsize=12)
plt.ylabel("Hour of Day", fontsize=12)
plt.xticks(rotation=45)
plt.yticks(rotation=0)
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

Engagement rate vs. Sessions over time¶

In [81]:
df_plot = df.groupby("DateHour")[["Engagement rate", "Sessions"]].mean().reset_index()
plt.figure(figsize=(10,5))
plt.plot(df_plot["DateHour"], df_plot["Engagement rate"], label="Engagement Rate", color="brown")
plt.plot(df_plot["DateHour"], df_plot["Sessions"], label="Sessions", color="darkviolet")
plt.title("Engagement Rate vs. Sessions Over Time")
plt.xlabel("Date Hour")
plt.xticks(rotation =90)
plt.legend()
plt.grid(True)
plt.show()
